            [
                'title' => 'Leadership in Crisis: Guiding Your Team Through Uncertainty',
                'content' => "Crisis situations test leadership like nothing else. Whether it's economic downturns, industry disruptions, or global events, strong leadership can make the difference between survival and failure.\n\n**Crisis Leadership Principles:**\n\n1. **Communicate Transparently**\n   - Share what you know and what you don't\n   - Provide regular updates\n   - Be honest about challenges\n   - Acknowledge emotions and concerns\n\n2. **Make Decisions Quickly**\n   - Gather available information rapidly\n   - Accept that perfect information isn't always possible\n   - Communicate decisions clearly\n   - Be prepared to adjust course\n\n3. **Focus on What You Can Control**\n   - Identify controllable vs. uncontrollable factors\n   - Channel energy into actionable solutions\n   - Help team focus on their sphere of influence\n\n**Supporting Your Team:**\n\n• **Emotional Support**\n  - Acknowledge stress and anxiety\n  - Provide mental health resources\n  - Encourage work-life balance\n  - Lead by example in self-care\n\n• **Practical Support**\n  - Clarify roles and expectations\n  - Provide necessary tools and resources\n  - Remove obstacles and bureaucracy\n  - Offer flexibility where possible\n\n• **Professional Development**\n  - Use downtime for training\n  - Cross-train team members\n  - Invest in skill development\n  - Prepare for post-crisis opportunities\n\n**Strategic Thinking in Crisis:**\n\n1. **Scenario Planning**\n   - Develop multiple future scenarios\n   - Create contingency plans\n   - Identify early warning indicators\n   - Build flexibility into operations\n\n2. **Opportunity Recognition**\n   - Look for market gaps created by crisis\n   - Identify ways to serve customers better\n   - Consider strategic partnerships\n   - Invest in innovation\n\n**Communication Framework:**\n\n• **What** - Clear facts and information\n• **Why** - Context and reasoning\n• **How** - Specific actions and next steps\n• **When** - Timelines and milestones\n• **Who** - Roles and responsibilities\n\n**Building Resilience:**\n- Celebrate small wins and progress\n- Maintain team traditions and culture\n- Encourage innovation and creativity\n- Learn from setbacks and adapt\n- Plan for recovery and growth\n\nRemember: Crisis reveals character. Use these challenging times to strengthen your leadership skills and build a more resilient organization.",
                'status' => Tip::STATUS_DRAFT,
                'published_at' => null,
                'claps' => 0,
