                'title' => 'Sustainable Business Practices: Profit with Purpose',
                'content' => "Sustainability isn't just good for the planet - it's good for business. Companies with strong sustainability practices often see improved profitability, customer loyalty, and employee engagement.\n\n**Why Sustainability Matters:**\n\n• **Consumer Demand**\n  - 73% of consumers willing to pay more for sustainable products\n  - Millennials and Gen Z prioritize environmental responsibility\n  - Brand reputation increasingly tied to sustainability\n\n• **Cost Savings**\n  - Energy efficiency reduces operational costs\n  - Waste reduction improves margins\n  - Sustainable practices often increase efficiency\n\n• **Risk Management**\n  - Regulatory compliance and future-proofing\n  - Supply chain resilience\n  - Access to sustainable financing\n\n**Getting Started:**\n\n1. **Sustainability Audit**\n   - Assess current environmental impact\n   - Identify areas for improvement\n   - Set baseline measurements\n   - Benchmark against industry standards\n\n2. **Quick Wins**\n   - Switch to LED lighting\n   - Implement recycling programs\n   - Reduce paper usage\n   - Optimize heating and cooling\n\n3. **Strategic Initiatives**\n   - Sustainable sourcing policies\n   - Green product development\n   - Carbon footprint reduction\n   - Circular economy principles\n\n**Implementation Areas:**\n\n• **Operations**\n  - Energy management systems\n  - Waste reduction and recycling\n  - Water conservation\n  - Sustainable transportation\n\n• **Supply Chain**\n  - Vendor sustainability requirements\n  - Local sourcing when possible\n  - Ethical labor practices\n  - Packaging optimization\n\n• **Products/Services**\n  - Eco-friendly design principles\n  - Product lifecycle assessment\n  - Repair and refurbishment programs\n  - Digital alternatives to physical products\n\n**Measuring Impact:**\n- Carbon footprint tracking\n- Waste diversion rates\n- Energy consumption metrics\n- Water usage monitoring\n- Sustainable sourcing percentages\n\n**Communication Strategy:**\n- Be authentic and transparent\n- Share progress and challenges\n- Avoid greenwashing\n- Engage stakeholders in sustainability journey\n- Celebrate milestones and achievements\n\n**Business Benefits:**\n- Reduced operational costs\n- Enhanced brand reputation\n- Improved employee morale\n- Access to new markets\n- Increased customer loyalty\n- Better risk management\n\nSustainability is not a destination but a continuous journey of improvement. Start with small steps and build momentum over time.",
                'status' => Tip::STATUS_ARCHIVED,
                'published_at' => now()->subDays(30),
                'claps' => 12,
